<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-30T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-30T05:00:00-05:00" n="604" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d604">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2600</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Denmark</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GSU1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-30T11:00:00+01:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 30, 1918, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.09 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2711. The Danish Minister at Petrograd has telegraphed to the Minister of
                            Foreign Affairs announcing the appearance of a Bolshevik decree ordering
                            the arrest of all subjects or citizens of the <pb facs="0736" n="662" xml:id="pg_662"/> Associated Governments between the ages of 18 and
                            45. I further learn that the announcements of Bolshevik victories over
                            the Czechoslovaks have been chiefly fabrications and that the early fall
                            of Vyatka and Perm is expected. Copy to London.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_GSU1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Grant-Smith</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>